 state of equilibrium. The book uncovers some interesting findings that will significantly contribute to the literature on ethnic tourism in developing areas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCulture and tourismzChinazHainan Sheng . 0aCulture and tourismzChinazHainan Sheng. 0aEthnic groupszChinazHainan Sheng . 0aEthnic groupszChinazHainan Sheng. 0aTourismzChinazHainan Sheng . 0aTourismzChinazHainan Sheng. 4aAnthropology. 4aSociology. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aChina.  aHainan Island.  aauthenticity.  adeveloping areas.  aethnic tourism development.  astakeholder interaction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCVP eBook-Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311075437740uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184541159640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845411596423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781845411596.jpg  a978-3-11-075437-7  CVP eBook-Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK